President Obama has awarded the National Medal of Science and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation to 17 individuals for their contributions to science, engineering, and invention. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made outstanding contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation recognizes those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The recipients include scientists and innovators from various fields, including nanoscience, algebraic geometry, social learning mechanisms, microbiology, physics, oncology, genetics, environmental science, and material science. Their work has had a profound impact on society and serves as an inspiration for future generations in the fields of science, technology, engineering, and math.